<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Schematic Name="CD4013 sub-octave (Rocktave-style)" Description="Classic divide-by-2 sub-octave: input buffer feeds a high-gain op-amp comparator that squares the guitar signal, the square wave clocks a CD4013 D flip-flop wired in toggle mode (D tied to Q-bar), and Q drives a sub-octave square wave into a blend pot mixed with the dry signal. Reference: hammer.ampage.org Rocktave divider, valvewizard.co.uk/uboat." PartNumber="">
